The article discusses the commemoration of World AIDS Day and the commitment to fighting HIV/AIDS. The Biden-Harris Administration is dedicated to implementing the National HIV/AIDS Strategy and ending the HIV epidemic globally. The article also highlights the 20th anniversary of the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) and its impact in supporting countries worldwide. However, barriers to comprehensive HIV prevention and treatment, as well as stigma and discrimination, continue to hinder progress. The Administration has taken various actions to accelerate domestic and global HIV efforts, address stigma and discrimination, ensure equity, support and treat at-risk populations, and advance new research.